# Bounded Context Verticals & Event Spine

## Decisions (locked)

- Pricing write-path: **WorkPrice only**. Estimate / ItemPrice — kill (no new usage).
- Inter-BC communication: **sync domain events only** (no queues in this refactor).
- Inventory write-off from order UI: **Inventory command + event** (Order does not orchestrate Inventory).

## Vertical isolation

Each BC is a vertical: `Domain → Application → Infrastructure` (+ own HTTP/Filament adapter if needed).

**Forbidden**

- Application handler of BC-A calling Repository / Handler / Eloquent of BC-B
- Application importing `App\Infrastructure\*\Model` (use ports / repositories only)
- UI (Filament / Vue API controller) calling handlers of **two** BCs in one action as an orchestrator
- Cross-BC “convenience” sync method calls instead of domain events

**Allowed**

- UI → **one** write command of the owning BC
- Aggregate mutates → records domain events → save → **publish inside same DB transaction**
- Listener (Infrastructure, thin) → Application command of the **target** BC
- Own-BC ReadPort for queries; cross-BC read only via dedicated read model / port (never via foreign write stack)

## Transactional Unit of Work

Initiating write use-case owns one outer transaction:

1. Load aggregate (source BC)
2. Mutate + record domain events
3. Persist aggregate
4. `DomainEventPublisher::publish` **inside the same transaction**
5. Sync listeners run Application commands of other BCs on the **same connection**
6. Any exception → **full rollback** of source + all reactions

**Rules**

- Do not open nested `DB::transaction()` in listeners blindly
- Critical listeners must be idempotent w.r.t. FSM
- Queries / ReadPorts stay outside write transactions

## Event listener shape

```
Infrastructure\Listener\XOnY
  → Application\<TargetBc>\Command\...Handler
```

Listener must not contain business rules or Eloquent writes beyond delegating to Application.

Catalog: `docs/architecture/domain-event-catalog.md` — every domain event is **LIVE** or **FUTURE_HOOK**. No silent orphan listener classes.

## Service types

Sharpening vs repair branching lives in Application **Strategy** packages:

- `Application\Order\ServiceType\*` — order item build
- `Application\Workshop\WorkAttachment\*` — work target
- `Application\Workshop\ServiceType\*` — production completion
- `Application\Pricing\ServiceType\*` — pricing presentation

Not scattered UI if/else on `service_type` strings when a policy already exists.
